.TH CONFLUENCE 1 "2025-11-24" "Project Chronos 2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
confluence \- Confluence page management CLI tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B confluence
[\fIOPTION\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B confluence
provides full CRUD operations for managing Confluence pages from the command line.
Supports markdown-to-Confluence conversion, Jira integration, and page hierarchy management.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B create
Create a new Confluence page
.TP
.B read
Read page details
.TP
.B update
Update an existing page
.TP
.B delete
Delete a page
.TP
.B list
List pages in a space
.TP
.B add-comment
Add a comment to a page
.TP
.B list-comments
List comments on a page
.SH CREATE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-title " " \fITITLE\fR
Page title (required)
.TP
.BR \-\-space " " \fISPACE\fR
Confluence space key (required, e.g., PC)
.TP
.BR \-\-body " " \fIBODY\fR
Inline page content in markdown format
.TP
.BR \-\-body\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Path to markdown file for page content
.TP
.BR \-\-parent " " \fIPARENT\fR
Parent page title (for page hierarchy)
.TP
.BR \-\-labels " " \fILABELS\fR
Comma-separated labels
.TP
.BR \-\-jira\-ticket " " \fITICKET\fR
Link to Jira ticket (e.g., CHRONOS-167)
.TP
.BR \-\-banner
Add read-only banner to page (auto-generated from Git notice)
.SH UPDATE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-new\-title " " \fITITLE\fR
New page title (rename page)
.TP
.BR \-\-body " " \fIBODY\fR
New inline content in markdown
.TP
.BR \-\-body\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Path to markdown file with new content
.TP
.BR \-\-labels " " \fILABELS\fR
Replace all labels with new comma-separated list
.TP
.BR \-\-banner
Add read-only banner to page (auto-generated from Git notice)
.SH COMMENT OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-space " " \fISPACE\fR
Confluence space key (required)
.TP
.BR \-\-text " " \fITEXT\fR
Comment text (required for add-comment)
.SH LIST OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-space " " \fISPACE\fR
Confluence space key (required)
.TP
.BR \-\-limit " " \fILIMIT\fR
Number of results to return (default: 20)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create page from inline content:
.B confluence create
\-\-title "Page Title" \-\-space PC \-\-body "# Content"
.TP
Create page from file with banner:
.B confluence create
\-\-title "Sprint 4 Summary" \-\-space PC \-\-body\-file summary.md \-\-labels "sprint,documentation" \-\-banner
.TP
Create page with Jira link:
.B confluence create
\-\-title "Bug Fix (CHRONOS-167)" \-\-space PC \-\-body\-file fix.md \-\-jira\-ticket CHRONOS-167
.TP
Read page:
.B confluence read
"Page Title" \-\-space PC
.TP
Update page content:
.B confluence update
"Page Title" \-\-space PC \-\-body\-file updated.md
.TP
Rename page:
.B confluence update
"Old Title" \-\-space PC \-\-new\-title "New Title"
.TP
List pages:
.B confluence list
\-\-space PC \-\-limit 10
.TP
Delete page:
.B confluence delete
"Page Title" \-\-space PC
.TP
Add comment:
.B confluence add-comment
"Page Title" \-\-space PC \-\-text "Great work!"
.TP
List comments:
.B confluence list-comments
"Page Title" \-\-space PC
